However the above posting is incredibly astute, that it's easily misconstrued for the truth because we all know people like that in game and I do mean all of us. Everyone of us, including you Ghie, has met someone who plays 20 hours a day, neglects their responsibilities, and only plays the game for loot, even if you don't know it.<br>
<br>
Everyday people on this board get labelled as, scammers and loot whores. What is a scammer or a loot whore but someone who has forsaken friendship for loot?<br>
<br>
I've met dozens of people who think they're better then another person because of the things they do in game or the loot they have. I see it each and every time I log on. The sad thing is not that we've been unlucky enough to meet these people but that you've been unlucky enough not to recognize them.<br>
<br>
 <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://ak.lonelygamer.com">
<IMG SRC="http://www.plattsflello.com/ryn.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulonchin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lonchin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/2/02 7:02:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3447.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Uberitis</span><hr size=1> Uberitis, that disease which can afflict all players.  I see victims of uberitis a lot now.  When we were lower level characters we would group with a great many other players in the full range of levels permitted.  We learned from each other, we met new players formed friendships, laughed and enjoyed the company of strangers without giving thought to anything but the fresh enjoyment the game brought to us.<br>
<br>
Now that we have reached higher levels, our uberitis makes us think that if a person is 3 or 4 levels lower than us then they are unworthy of our company.  We use arguments such as too risky, you will get agro, your not high enough for this etc.  What really is happening is our behaviour has been warped by Uberitis, that dread disease.  Uberitis, I fear there is no cure for you, for no matter what we do, the gods of Verant will be feeding this beast of uberitis so that we will want more, more more.<br>
<br>
May the Gods have mercy on us all.<br>
